|Technique=Technique/T1065
|Description=Some {{LinkThisPage}} malware uses a list of ordered port numbers to choose a port for C2 traffic, which includes uncommonly used ports such as 995, 1816, 465, 1521, 3306, and many others.[[CiteRef::Novetta Blockbuster RATs]]
}}{{Technique Object
|Technique=Technique/T1067
|Description={{LinkThisPage}} malware WhiskeyAlfa-Three modifies sector 0 of the Master Boot Record (MBR) to ensure that the malware will persist even if a victim machine shuts down.[[CiteRef::Novetta Blockbuster Destructive Malware]]
